<DOC><DOCNO> AP890111-0270 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-01-11-89 2250EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f AM-GasPipeline     01-11 0121</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Gas Pipeline,0126</SECOND><HEAD>Construction of 1,000-Mile Pipeline To Begin In 1989</HEAD><DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Coastal Corp. announced Wednesday it wouldbegin construction this year of a 1,000-mile natural gas pipelinefrom southwestern Wyoming to California.   The $665 million project, given final approval by the FederalEnergy Regulatory Commission on Wednesday, will eventually transport400 million cubic feet of gas a day from Wyoming, Coastal said.   The gas will be used mainly to generate steam for recoveringheavy oil from California wells.   Harold Burrow, chairman of WyCal and vice chairman of Coastal,said the pipeline will begin transporting gas to California by early1991.   Colorado Interstate Gas Co., a subsidiary of Coastal, will buildand operate the project, Burrow said.</TEXT></DOC>